snippet.textDisplay: I remember when I heard about there being a location called "Hidden Village" in Twilight Princess, I assumed it was, like, a secret town that you could discover by exploring or doing a special sidequest, and I thought that sounded cool. snippet.textDisplay: Twilight Princess' dungeons are varied, long and challenging. When I played, I'd almost get a claustrophobic sensation while being deep in the dungeons, the same one I get when going through some of the Metroid series' areas. When I'd finally complete a dungeon and step﻿ outside after hours of great puzzles and battles, I wouldn't have been surprised if Link spoke for the first time just to say﻿ he was glad to see the sun and breathe fresh air again.

snippet.textDisplay: I think it's the first time in the list I upload a track from the same series twice in a row! I actually find Twilight Princess has a couple of flaws, including the overlong tutorial, the mostly bland overworld and unappealing character design (I did like Link, Zelda and Midna though!). However, it completely makes up for it with my favorite dungeons and bosses in the series. That and some very unique and fun items (spinner, ball and chain, double clawshot, etc.).
